-- Origin shares up over 4 pct on BG hostile bid
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2008 9:22pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/24/us-origin-shares-idUSSYU00459120080624

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Shares in Australia's Origin Energy Ltd ( ORG.AX ) rose more than 4 percent on Tuesday after British gas producer BG Group ( BG.L ) launched a hostile A$13.8 billion ($13.1 billion) bid for Origin.  

 By 9:11 p.m. EDT, Origin shares were up 4.5 percent at A$16.20, compared with BG's offer price of A$15.50 each, while the broader market .AXJO was down 0.6 percent.
   ($1=A$1.05) (Reporting by  Denny Thomas )